Citation.sTitle: Investigation of Potassium Sulphate - Calcium Sulphate Binary System by Knudsen Effusion Mass  Spectrometry
Citation.sAbstract: Vaporisation studies of pure K2SO4 and mixtures of K2SO4 and CaSO4 in the quasi-binary  K2SO4-CaSO4 system with Knudsen effusion mass spectrometry resulted in the determination of  thermodynamic data. From partial pressures of the gaseous species over condensed phases it was  possible to determine the sublimation enthalpies AsubH and the thermodynamic activities of  components. The sublimation enthalpy of K2SO4 agrees well with two literature sources. For the first  time the experimental data of activities of K2SO4 and CaSO4 in the binary system could confirm  theoretical studies.
